ROW (1, "Super Luck", NULL, 'Passive', 1, NULL, "Increases Critical-Hit rate by 15%", NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
ROW (1, "Attack", NULL, 'Basic', 1, NULL, "Becomes a boosted attack with every third attack, dealing damage to enemies and lowering their Defense by 15% for 2s when it hits. If this boosted attack hits only a single target, it deals increased damage.", 'Physical', 1.00, 0, 0),
ROW (1, "Feint", 'Dash', 'Move1', 1, 8, "Absol dashes in an arc, damaging all enemies hit. Each use alternates between a left and right arc. Feint ignores the target's Defense and bypasses all shields.", 'Physical', 0.66, 7, 130),
ROW (1, "Night Slash", 'Dash', 'Move1', 5, 5, "Absol dashes in an arc, damaging the first Pokémon hit. If Absol hits, this ability can be activated within 6s – allowing Absol to dash again, dealing damage to all enemies hit and increasing attack speed once again. The second hit also has 30% increased Critical-Hit Rate on enemies below 50% max HP.

Cooldown on Hit or without recasting is 6s.", 'Physical', 0.69, 6, 140),
ROW (1, "Night Slash Upgrade", 'Dash', 'Move1', 11, 5, "Absol heals for 50% of damage dealt on the second hit, including critical hits.", 'Physical', 0.69, 6, 140),
ROW (1, "Pursuit", 'Dash', 'Move1', 5, 5, "Absol dashes to a location, and dashes to an enemy with its next auto attack. If Absol hits the back of the target, this ability's cooldown is reduced by 80%. If it fails to hit the back, damage is reduced. The next auto attack stays empowered for 3s.", 'Physical', 1.10, 9, 140),
ROW (1, "Pursuit Upgrade", 'Dash', 'Move1', 11, 5, "Absol gains 35% increased movement speed for 2s after the initial dash.", 'Physical', 1.10, 9, 140),
ROW (1, "Slash", 'Melee', 'Move2', 1, 6, "Absol quickly slashes in front of themself, damaging any enemy hit by the slash. Slash has an increased critical-hit rate by 15%.", 'Physical', 0.89, 6, 200),
ROW (1, "Psycho Cut", 'Ranged', 'Move2', 7, 7, "Throw a wide slash forward; damaging and slowing enemies hit by 90% for 2s. This slow decreases by 25% every 0.5s. Enemies hit are marked for 5s with 3 cleansable marks. The first two deal 2x damage when triggered, the third deals 3x damage. When Absol deals damage to a marked enemy, a mark is consumed, dealing extra damage.

All damage dealt by Psycho Cut or its marks have a 15% increased Critical-Hit Rate.", 'Physical', 0.30, 2, 45),
ROW (1, "Psycho Cut Upgrade", 'Ranged', 'Move2', 13, 7, "Increases Absol's movement speed by 20% when near a debuffed enemy.", 'Physical', 0.30, 2, 45),
ROW (1, "Sucker Punch", 'Sure Hit', 'Move2', 7, 6, "Absol targets an enemy and enters a counter stance for 1s, decreasing the movement speed of the target enemy and Absol by 50% for the duration and negating all damage and effects of the next attack on Absol. While in counter stance, if Absol is attacked or the target attacks, Absol immediately exits counter stance and leaps behind the target, stunning it and dealing damage. If the attack is not triggered before the counter stance expires, Absol leaps behind the target, stunning them and dealing damage.", 'Physical', 1.05, 6, 165),
ROW (1, "Sucker Punch Upgrade", 'Melee', 'Move2', 13, 6, "Increases Attack Speed by 40% for 3s after using this move.", 'Physical', 1.05, 6, 165),
ROW (1, "Midnight Slash", 'Area', 'Unite', 9, 134, "Unleash a flurry of 5 slashes in front of Absol and become untargetable for 1.15s. This move ends by unleashing powerful blades of energy, shoving enemies and dealing damage up to 4 times at melee range and down to 1 time at maximum range. Only the first ending hit connecting with an enemy does full damage, the others, deal 30% damage to the same target.", 'Physical', 0.91, 4, 200),

ROW (2, "No Guard", NULL, 'Passive', 1, NULL, "Honedge and Doublade do not gain the stat benefits of Stance Change. However, their boosted attack functions like Aegislash's Sword Stance boosted attack.", NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
ROW (2, "Stance Change", NULL, 'Passive', 1, NULL, "Aegislash can switch between Sword Stance and Shield Stance. Using a blade move switches stance to Sword Stance; which increases Attack, movement speed by 5%, and Attack Speed by 15%. Using a shield move switches stance to Shield Stance; which increases Defense and Sp. Defense and reduces Attack Speed by 20%. After switching stances, movement speed and basic attack speed are further increased by 15% for 3.5s.", NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
ROW (2, "Attack", NULL, 'Basic', 1, NULL, "Slash at enemies in front of Aegislash, dealing damage to them. If the boost count is one or more, auto attacks become a boosted attack. When in Sword Stance or No Guard: pierce through enemies, dealing damage. When in Shield Stance: ram enemies, dealing damage and leaving them unable to act for .1s, restore HP, and reduce the cooldown of Sacred Sword and Shadow Claw by 1s when this attack hits. Every boosted attack consumes one boost count. Up to 4 boosted attacks can be stored.", 'Physical', 1.00, 0, 0),
ROW (2, "Shadow Sneak", 'Dash', 'Move1', 1, 6, "Cast a shadow in the designated direction dealing damage to enemies hit. After the shadow hits an enemy or travels its maximum distance, Aegislash warps to the shadow's location, dealing damage to nearby enemies and increase boost count by 1.", 'Physical', 0.93, 8, 150),
ROW (2, "Sacred Sword", 'Area', 'Move1', 5, 7.5, "Aegislash thrusts its blade into the ground creating a triangular zone. This zone erupts with a hidden power, dealing damage to enemies in the area and throws them in the air for .6s. Also increases boost count by 1 for each enemy hit (capped at 2 for wilds, 4 for players). At the same time as the eruption, Aegislash slashes forward, dealing additional damage to enemies hit. For 3s after this slash hits, damage dealt by Aegislash ignores 25% of the enemy's Defense.", 'Physical', 0.96, 3, 120),
ROW (2, "Sacred Sword Upgrade", 'Area', 'Move1', 11, 7.5, "Increase Attack by 50 for 3s after hitting enemies with the triangle attack.", 'Physical', 0.96, 3, 120),
ROW (2, "Shadow Claw", 'Dash', 'Move1', 5, 5.5, "Aegislash slashes with its blade twice in the designated direction, dealing damage to enemies hit. Follow up with a final rising slash that deals damage to enemies hit and throws them in the air for .75s. Boost count increases by 1 when at least one of the three slashes hits.", 'Physical', 0.63, 3, 70),
ROW (2, "Shadow Claw Upgrade", 'Dash', 'Move1', 11, 5.5, "Increases Critical-Hit Rate by 20% for 1s (This move does not benefit).", 'Physical', 0.63, 3, 70),
ROW (2, "Iron Defense", 'Buff', 'Move2', 1, 7, "Envelops Aegislash in a powerful protective force for 3s or after blocking one attack. If this move blocks an attack, increase boost count by 1.", NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
ROW (2, "Wide Guard", 'Buff', 'Move2', 7, 9, "Focus in place for a short time to create a great shield on Aegislash for 1.2s. When this great shield appears, boost count increases by 1, grants a shield to Aegislash and shoves enemies in front. While the shield persists, Aegislash is Unstoppable and incoming damage increases boost count by 1 for each different source (capping at 2). When this move ends, shove enemies for .75s in front of Aegislash once again and slow them by 45% for 2s.

Gain 1 boosted count if the shove at the end hits at least one enemy. If the great shield is depleted before the duration of this move ends, the boosted count is granted regardless of whether an enemy is hit.", 'Physical', 2.00, 0, 400),
ROW (2, "Wide Guard Upgrade", 'Buff', 'Move2', 13, 9, "Cooldown reduced by 1s.", 'Physical', 2.00, 0, 400),
ROW (2, "Iron Head", 'Buff', 'Move2', 7, 7, "Dash in the designated direction dealing damage to enemies hit. Also increases boost count by 1, and protects Aegislash with a special shield for 1s afterward. This shield doesn't protect from hindrances, but it can nullify damage. When the shield blocks an attack, it disappears, the cooldown is reduced by 3s, and boost count is increased by 1.", 'Physical', 1.18, 5, 130),
ROW (2, "Iron Head Upgrade", 'Buff', 'Move2', 13, 7, "If an attack is blocked with this move, Aegislash gains +10% Attack for 3s.", 'Physical', 1.18, 5, 130),
ROW (2, "Coup de Grace", 'Area', 'Unite', 9, 100, "Unleash a ground-splitting slash in the designated direction dealing damage to enemies hit and switching to Sword Stance. The lower their remaining HP, the more damage this move deals. If this slash knocks out an enemy, boost count increases by 2.", 'Physical', 2.82, 13, 640),

ROW (3, "Huge Power", NULL, 'Passive', 1, NULL, "When this Pokémon hits only a single enemy with an auto attack, a move, or their Unite Move, the hit is always a critical hit. However, when hitting two or more enemies at once with an auto attack, a move, or its Unite Move, the hits are never critical hits.

Critical hits deal 150% rather than 200%.", NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
ROW (3, "Attack", NULL, 'Basic', 1, NULL, "Becomes a boosted attack with every third attack, dealing increased damage to enemies within a cone area of effect in front of this Pokémon.", 'Physical', 1.00, 0, 0),
ROW (3, "Tackle", 'Dash', 'Move1', 1, 5, "Charge forward; dealing damage to any enemy hit and leave them unable to act for a short time.", 'Physical', 0.86, 8, 100),
ROW (3, "Play Rough", 'Buff', 'Move1', 6, 5, "Increase movement speed by 35% for 4s and change the next auto attack. When performing the next auto attack, lunge at one enemy in range and deliver repeated blows dealing damage to that target and leave it unable to act for .75s.

Using Play Rough will overwrite any active Aqua Tail attack change. Play Rough attacks count as auto attacks for the purpose of items, lifesteal and other benefits.", 'Physical', 0.39, 4, 60),
ROW (3, "Play Rough Upgrade", 'Buff', 'Move1', 12, 5, "Further increases movement speed when this move is used, and also reduces this move's cooldown by 1s.", 'Physical', 0.39, 4, 60),
ROW (3, "Water Pulse", 'Ranged', 'Move1', 6, 5, "Shoot a pulsing blast of water in front of Azumarill. When the blast of water hits an enemy, decrease their movement speed for 2s and deal damage to all enemies in an area of effect around the initial target. The blast of water then automatically bounces to another target if one is available. Including the first target, the blast of water can bounce between up to three targets consecutively, and each hit behaves in the same way as the first.

While the blast of water is travelling, Azumarill can perform a short rolling dash in a designated direction.", 'Physical', 0.87, 7, 120),
ROW (3, "Water Pulse Upgrade", 'Ranged', 'Move1', 12, 5, "Increase the maximum number of targets that the blast of water can bounce between by 2.", 'Physical', 0.87, 7, 120),
ROW (3, "Bubble", 'Area', 'Move2', 1, 6, "Spray bubbles in a cone dealing damage to enemies in the area of effect and decreasing their movement speed for a short time. This move can be used while moving.", 'Physical', 0.74, 7, 80),
ROW (3, "Whirlpool", 'Area', 'Move2', 4, 11, "For a short time, four small whirlpools appear that swirl around Azumarill as it moves. If a whirlpool hits an enemy, the whirlpool deals damage to them and restores Azumarill's HP. If a whirlpool hits an enemy player, an increased amount of HP is restored.

Moving clockwise against your target will grant more hits against that target, and counter-clockwise will reduce the number of hits.", 'Physical', 0.34, 2, 60),
ROW (3, "Whirlpool Upgrade", 'Area', 'Move2', 10, 11, "Reduces this move's cooldown by 2s and increases the amount of HP restored.", 'Physical', 0.34, 2, 60),
ROW (3, "Aqua Tail", 'Buff', 'Move2', 4, 7, "Increases the speed and area of effect of the next three auto attacks for 5s. If these auto attacks hit from a distance, they also deal increased damage and restore HP. Using Aqua Tail will overwrite any active Play Rough attack change.

Aqua Tail attacks count as auto attacks for the purpose of items, lifesteal and other benefits.", 'Physical', 0.68, 2, 50),
ROW (3, "Aqua Tail Upgrade", 'Buff', 'Move2', 10, 7, "Aqua Tail attacks that hit an enemy from a distance reduce the cooldown of all moves by 0.8s per enemy hit..", 'Physical', 0.68, 2, 50),
ROW (3, "Belly Bash", 'Sure Hit', 'Unite', 8, 89, "Azumarill targets a Pokémon and then pounds their belly three times; losing 5% remaining HP with each pound in exchange for a 5% max HP shield that stacks with each pound and lasts 6s. Azumarill also gains increased Attack for 5s and can move while pounding their belly. Azumarill then charges at the target damaging and throwing all Pokémon hit while charging and Pokémon within the area effect around the target.", 'Physical', 1.08, 9, 260),

